<TITLE> AL begins three-day mourning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League today started a three-day mourning programme over the death of Dr M A Wazed Miah, prime minister Sheikh Hasina's husband who died on Saturday. The ruling party hoisted black flag and kept the party flag at half-mast in the party offices across the country. The central working committee at a meeting on Sunday announced the mourning programme to pay tribute to Dr Miah, a nuclear scientist. AL deputy publicity secretary Ashim Kumar Ukil told bdnews24.com they had started three-day mourning programme. Doa and milad mahfil would be held at the party headquarters Monday afternoon, he said. AL spokesman Syed Ashraful Islam said they directed all party leaders and activists to observe the three-day mourning programme in the districts, Upazila and unions. The programmes of the next two days include offering special prayer at mosques, temples and churches across the country on Tuesday and arranging citizen commemoration meeting on Wednesday. Dr Miah was buried at his family graveyard in his village home at Pirganj, Rangpur on Sunday. His qulkhwani will be held on Thursday at the prime minister's official residence Jamuna. bdne
